Genital capsule
: Aedeagal shaft flattened laterally, C-shaped, arising from concave plate, formed by circular dorsal apodeme and preatrium; gonopore subapical, caudad; shaft short, 1.4 times as long as dorsal apodeme (
Figs 69
, 
96
). Connective elongate (
Fig. 123
). Plate elongate, apex rounded, base fused with valve (
Fig. 148
). Pygofer lobe apex broadly rounded (
Figs 173
, 
198
). Style apophysis rectangular, serrate ventrally; extending one-third from apex of plate; apophysis 0.6 times as long as anterior lateral lobe (
Fig. 224
).
